cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.SE 

The paper describes the use of answer set programming to construct an automated system for music composition, which involves knowledge representation and logical reasoning. This fits well with the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves the analysis and verification of compositions, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the system has potential for live performances and concerts, which could relate to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
